  "text": "The xDS DiscoveryResponse processing in Envoy follows this chain:\n\n## 1. gRPC Stream Reception\nAt the lowest level, `GrpcStream` (source/extensions/config_subscription/grpc/grpc_stream.h) receives DiscoveryResponse messages from the management server via gRPC. The `onReceiveMessage()` method (line 85) is called when a message arrives, which immediately invokes `callbacks_->onDiscoveryResponse(std::move(message), control_plane_stats_)` (line 95). The stream also manages connection establishment via `establishNewStream()` (line 51) and handles reconnection with backoff strategy.\n\n## 2. Response Handling & Validation\nThe `GrpcMuxImpl::onDiscoveryResponse()` method (source/extensions/config_subscription/grpc/grpc_mux_impl.cc, line 313) serves as the main entry point. It performs initial validation:\n- Checks that there are active watches for the resource type_url (line 319)\n- Tracks control plane identity from message metadata (lines 329-337)\n- Validates that resource type_urls match the message-wide type_url (lines 369-374)\n- Detects and filters out heartbeat responses (line 379)\n- Calls external config validators via `config_validators_->executeValidators()` (line 452 in processDiscoveryResources)\n\nFor responses with errors, exception handling wraps resource ingestion (lines 363-406).\n\n## 3. Resource Version Bookkeeping\nVersion tracking is implemented in two places:\n\nFor State-of-the-World (SotW): `GrpcMuxImpl::ApiState` (source/extensions/config_subscription/grpc/grpc_mux_impl.h, line 231) maintains per-type_url state including:\n- `request_` field containing the current `version_info` (line 241)\n- `control_plane_identifier_` to track response source (line 253)\n- Nonce management for ACK/NACK sequencing (line 341)\n\nAfter processing, `api_state.request_.set_version_info(version_info)` (grpc_mux_impl.cc, line 513) updates the tracked version.\n\nFor Delta xDS: `DeltaSubscriptionState` (source/extensions/config_subscription/grpc/delta_subscription_state.h, line 78) implements per-resource version tracking:\n- `ResourceState` class (lines 113-139) maintains individual resource versions\n- `requested_resource_state_` map tracks versions of explicitly requested resources (line 151)\n- `wildcard_resource_state_` map tracks versions from wildcard subscriptions (line 154)\n- `handleResponse()` method (line 94) processes DeltaDiscoveryResponse with nonce handling (delta_subscription_state.cc, line 142)\n- `handleGoodResponse()` updates resource versions via `addResourceStateFromServer()` (line 185-263)\n\n## 4. Listener/Cluster Update Dispatch\nThe dispatch mechanism uses the `WatchMap` (source/extensions/config_subscription/grpc/watch_map.h/cc):\n\n`GrpcMuxImpl::processDiscoveryResources()` (grpc_mux_impl.cc, line 413) builds a resource reference map and calls watch callbacks:\n- Iterates through all watches (line 455)\n- For each watch, finds matching resources either by explicit name or wildcard (lines 466-481)\n- Calls `watch->callbacks_.onConfigUpdate(found_resources, version_info)` (line 487) for cluster/listener updates\n\n`WatchMap::onConfigUpdate()` (watch_map.cc, line 128) receives decoded resources and:\n- Finds all watches interested in each resource via `watchesInterestedIn()` (line 147)\n- Builds per-watch update bundles (lines 145-154)\n- Executes validators (line 157)\n- Delivers updates: calls `watch->callbacks_.onConfigUpdate()` with resource bundles (line 176 or 180)\n- Caches EDS resources if applicable (lines 184-199)\n\n## 5. Configuration Application\nThe `SubscriptionCallbacks` interface (invoked at line 176/180 in watch_map.cc) connects to higher-level managers:\n- Cluster subscriptions implement `onConfigUpdate()` to apply cluster configuration\n- Listener subscriptions implement `onConfigUpdate()` to apply listener configuration\n- Route subscriptions apply routing updates\n- Endpoint subscriptions update load assignment for cluster endpoints\n\n## Key Protocol Elements\nThe xDS protocol definition (api/envoy/service/discovery/v3/discovery.proto) defines:\n- `DiscoveryResponse` (line 100): Contains resources, type_url, version_info, and nonce\n- `DeltaDiscoveryResponse` (line 143+): Contains added/removed resources with system_version_info\n- Resources are typed as google.protobuf.Any with embedded type information\n\n## New xDS Mux Implementation\nA newer implementation in `source/extensions/config_subscription/grpc/xds_mux/grpc_mux_impl.h` provides an alternative templated design supporting both SotW and Delta modes, but follows the same conceptual flow through `onDiscoveryResponse()` to subscription state handlers to watch map dispatching."
